  "bio_raw": "Nasir Uddin Ahmed is a skilled Data Scientist and Web Developer with a strong academic background, holding an MSc in Data Science (Distinction) from Universiti Malaya and a BSc in Computer Science and Engineering (Magna Cum Laude) from United International University. As the Co-founder and CTO of Hadodo IT Ltd., he leads innovative tech projects focused on ESG and sustainability. Nasir has extensive experience in data analysis, software development, and AI research, with published papers on sentiment analysis and music mood classification, Cyberbully Detection. Proficient in tools like Apache Spark, Python, and BERT-based models, he is passionate about driving innovation, solving complex problems, and contributing to Industry 4.0 advancements through research and strategic leadership.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "AI, Machine Learning, Data Analytics, Big Data Management, NLP, XAI, Data Science"
  ],
  "education": [
    {
      "raw": "Education\nMaster of Data Science\n(University of Malaya, Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia)\nBachelor of Science in Computer Science and Engineering\n(United International University, Dhaka, Bangladesh)"
    }
  ],
  "publications_raw": [
    "Conference Proceedings\nAhmed, N. U., Ismail, M. A., Rafiq, M. S., & Herawan, T. (2026). Cyberbully Detection in Sports on Social Media. In Frontier in Computer Science and Information Technology: Proceedings of FOCUS 2024. Lecture Notes on Data Engineering and Communications Technologies. Springer Nature. [In Press]\nHossain, M.K., Ahmed, N.U., Ahmed, M.F. (2025). A Transformer-Based Approach for Real-Time Sentiment Analysis of Transliterated Bengali Text. In: Palaiahnakote, S., Palit, R., Saraee, M., Atrey, P.K., Bai, X., Raman, B. (eds) Data Science, AI and Applications. ICDSAIA 2025. Communications in Computer and Information Science, vol 2681. Springer, Cham.\nhttps://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-\n032-11335-1_\nUrmi, N. P.,\nAhmed, N. U.\n, Sifat, M. H. R., Islam, S., & Jameel, A. S. M. M. (2021). Bangla Music MooD: A Music Mood Classifier from Bangla Music Lyrics. In J. S. Raj (Ed.), International Conference on Mobile Computing and Sustainable Informatics (pp. 673–681). Cham: Springer International Publishing.",
